  <action>
    1) Read the existing `## In-process RW→RO reopen of the same DB hangs (Phase 62 OverrideContext leak)` section in `.planning/milestones/v0.9.0-phases/63-readonly-database-load-support/deferred-items.md` (locate via grep `In-process RW→RO reopen` — read the full section to its terminating heading). Preserve the existing content. APPEND a new paragraph at the end of the section:

       ```
       **Resolved in v0.9.1 Phase 65 (B-prime architecture).** Eliminated all long-lived
       extension-owned `duckdb_connection` handles. Catalog reads now run on per-call
       C++ `Connection(*context.db)` derived from the caller's live `ClientContext`,
       scope-bounded by `ConnGuard` RAII (Rust) and `unique_ptr<Connection>` (C++).
       The catalog WRITE (CREATE/DROP/ALTER) still rides the Phase 58 rewrite-to-native
       path onto the caller's conn through the binder, preserving v0.8.0 transactional
       DDL semantics byte-identical.

       References:
       - `.planning/phases/65-overridecontext-connection-teardown/65-CONTEXT.md` (B-prime architecture)
       - `.planning/phases/65-overridecontext-connection-teardown/65-RESEARCH.md` §16 + §17 (mechanism + handle audit)
       - `.planning/phases/65-overridecontext-connection-teardown/65-OPTION-B-SPIKE.md` (PLAN-THREAD-RC0 empirical evidence)
       - `.planning/phases/65-overridecontext-connection-teardown/65-READ-PATH-SPIKE.md` (READ-BIND-RC0 empirical evidence)
       - `.planning/phases/65-overridecontext-connection-teardown/65-06-SUMMARY.md` (close-out)
       ```

    2) Read TECH-DEBT.md to find the existing numbering / formatting convention. Then APPEND two new entries at the end (or in numerical order if entries are numerically grouped — match existing style).

       TECH-DEBT 25 entry (full template — use whatever format matches existing entries):
       ```
       ## TECH-DEBT 25 — cached `duckdb_database` pointer Phase 62 defect (naturally resolved by Phase 65 B-prime)

       **Status:** Resolved in v0.9.1 Phase 65.
       **Filed:** 2026-05-XX (during Phase 65 close-out per CONTEXT D-15 / D-22).

       Phase 62 (v0.8.0) stashed the `duckdb_database` opaque pointer on
       `OverrideContext` at extension-load time. By query time the C-API path
       `duckdb_connect(stashed_db_handle)` returns rc=1 across all lifecycle
       phases (parse / bind / plan), while the C++ direct path
       `Connection(*context.db)` succeeds. Empirically isolated by
       `65-OPTION-B-SPIKE.md` Probe 1 vs Probe 2 split (same thread, same
       DatabaseInstance, microseconds apart, opposite results).

       Root cause: `duckdb_database` is reinterpreted as `DatabaseWrapper *`
       inside the C-API; by the time the request runs, the wrapper's internal
       `shared_ptr<DuckDB>` either points at a different DatabaseInstance than
       the live `context.db` or has been silently invalidated.

       **Resolution:** Phase 65 B-prime architecture never caches `db_handle`.
       All catalog reads and writes derive `Connection` from the live
       `ClientContext &` at call time. No cached pointer survives any callback's
       stack frame.

       **References:**
       - `.planning/phases/65-overridecontext-connection-teardown/65-OPTION-B-SPIKE.md`
       - `.planning/phases/65-overridecontext-connection-teardown/65-CONTEXT.md` (D-15)
       - `.planning/phases/65-overridecontext-connection-teardown/65-RESEARCH.md` §16.3
       ```

       TECH-DEBT 26 entry (or extend existing TECH-DEBT 19 — author's call; the simpler shape is a new entry):
       ```
       ## TECH-DEBT 26 — duckdb-rs BindInfo does not expose ClientContext / duckdb_database

       **Status:** Open (workaround shipped in Phase 65; upstream fix would simplify the surface).
       **Filed:** 2026-05-XX (during Phase 65 close-out per CONTEXT D-22).

       `duckdb::vtab::BindInfo` (the `&BindInfo` argument to the
       `register_table_function_with_extra_info` bind callback) does not expose
       the underlying `ClientContext &` or a way to obtain a `duckdb_database`.
       This forced Phase 65 to register the 14 read-side table functions + 2
       scalars directly through the C++ Catalog API
       (`Catalog::GetSystemCatalog(db).CreateTableFunction(CreateTableFunctionInfo{...})`),
       bypassing duckdb-rs entirely. Function bodies stay in Rust behind a thin
       FFI shim; only the registration plumbing moves into C++.

       The workaround adds ~150 LOC of C++ shim + Rust FFI surface (see
       `cpp/src/shim.cpp::sv_register_table_function` and per-function
       trampolines). It is correct and performant, but represents technical
       debt: any future read-side function added to the extension MUST go
       through the C++ shim until upstream duckdb-rs exposes a way for bind
       callbacks to reach `ClientContext &`.

       **Resolution path:** Upstream duckdb-rs PR to expose a method like
       `BindInfo::client_context() -> &ClientContext` or, at minimum,
       `BindInfo::database_handle() -> duckdb_database`. With that exposure
       the C++ Catalog API workaround can retire and registration shifts
       back to idiomatic duckdb-rs.

       **References:**
       - Plan 01 Spike A6 (`65-01-SPIKES.md`): empirical confirmation that
         `BindInfo` has no such accessor in duckdb-rs 1.10502.0.
       - `65-RESEARCH.md` §16.6 (C++ Catalog API registration template).
       - `65-READ-PATH-SPIKE.md` (READ-BIND-RC0): empirical viability of the
         workaround.

       **Related to (potentially supersedes):** TECH-DEBT 19 — DESCRIBE/SHOW
       read committed state was blocked on the same BindInfo gap. Under
       Phase 65 B-prime, DESCRIBE/SHOW now run on per-call probe connections
       derived from `*context.db`. They still see only committed state (the
       per-call conn inherits committed state at open time). TECH-DEBT 19's
       behaviour is unchanged from v0.9.0; it stays open until BindInfo
       exposes the live ClientContext, at which point both 19 and 26 close
       together.
       ```

